{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fairy|prevnum=682|prev=Spritzee|nextnum=684|next=Swirlix}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Aromatisse\n|jname=フレフワン\n|tmname=Frefuwan\n|jtranslit=Furefuwan\n|category=Fragrance\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fairy\n|ndex=683\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=130\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=34.2\n|weight-kg=15.5\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Healer\n|abilityd=Aroma Veil\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Fairy\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evhp=2\n|expyield=162\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Pink\n|catchrate=140\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=aromatisse\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Aromatisse\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'フレフワン\'\'\' \'\'Frefuwan\'\') is a {{type|Fairy}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Spritzee}} when [[trade]]d holding a [[Sachet]].\n\n==Biology==\nAromatisse is a bipedal, avian Pokémon. Its body is covered with fluffy purple feathers and around its lower body is an even fluffier mass of pink feathers. There is a black bow on its lower back. It has a white face with a small, curved beak that resembles a mask used by {{wp|plague doctor}}s or a {{wp|masquerade}} mask. Its eyes are black with red sclerae and pupils and full, black lashes. It has feathery ears with yellow centers. Each hand three yellow claws and it has paw-like feet with three toes. Aromatisse can give off a variety of different smells ranging from a pleasant fragrance to an odor so repugnant that it can turn a battle in its favor. In the past, {{m|Aromatic Mist}} was its [[signature move]].\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Aria Aromatisse.png|thumb|left|220px|Aromatisse in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nAn Aromatisse appeared in \'\'[[XY064|Battling with Elegance and a Big Smile!]]\'\', under the ownership of the reigning {{DL|Pokémon Performer|Kalos Queen}}, {{an|Aria}}. It made further appearances in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY090|Tag Team Battle Inspiration!]]\'\', and \'\'[[XY113|Performing a Pathway to the Future!]]\'\'.\n\nAn Aromatisse appeared in \'\'[[PK27|Pikachu and the Pokémon Music Squad]]\'\'. It noticed the fight between {{MTR}}, {{TP|Clemont|Chespin}}, and a {{p|Torchic}} over a [[Pecha Berry]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\nAromatisse debuted in \'\'[[XY039|Summer of Discovery!]]\'\' on a [[Pokévision]] video icon.\n{{-}}\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY064|Aromatisse|Serena\'s Pokédex|Aromatisse, the Fragrance Pokémon and the evolved form of Spritzee. Aromatisse can create many scents, some unpleasant enough to opponents to gain the advantage in battle.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Aromatisse (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fairy}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=130|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=fairy}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=X|